                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="471003" author="adilger" created="Thu, 11 Sep 2025 17:11:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As a starting point, I think we should only look at setting &lt;tt&gt;HS_EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; on directories that are part of an HSM imported tree (set via the Data Mover/copytool during directory tree creation, or manually afterward for existing filesystems), and not use &lt;tt&gt;HS_ARCHIVED&lt;/tt&gt; or other HSM states to indicate anything about the state of the files in that tree.  This is enough to determine that the directory is &lt;em&gt;part&lt;/em&gt; of an archive, and allow directory renames to be blocked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will almost certainly require some Lustre code changes to allow calling &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs hsm_set/state/clear &lt;em&gt;DIRECTORY&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to save the state on the directory instead of only on a regular file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="469621" author="JIRAUSER18483" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2025 09:37:20 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I moved the discussion about the details of what to do with this per-directory HSM state over to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19252&quot; title=&quot;option to disallow rename on archived files/directories&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19252&quot;&gt;LU-19252&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19252&quot; title=&quot;option to disallow rename on archived files/directories&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19252&quot;&gt;LU-19252&lt;/a&gt; is more how to allow renames or not rather than how to maintain the per-directory HSM state.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, for rename controls to be useful, directory rename control should be implemented, which is not straightforward :/&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Directory could be flagged as HSM Import and HSM Archived, from the parent directory up to filesystem root, stopping as soon as an already flagged directory is detected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tricky part is when to remove this flag? That could be done entry a directory entry is unlinked or moved out of it. But I&apos;m afraid of the performance implication of all of that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="466937" author="adilger" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2025 18:15:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I moved the discussion about the details of what to do with this per-directory HSM state over to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19252&quot; title=&quot;option to disallow rename on archived files/directories&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19252&quot;&gt;LU-19252&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="466936" author="adilger" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2025 17:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that this &quot;part of HSM archive directory tree&quot; state should not be confused with &quot;this directory tree is archived/stubbed&quot; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13024&quot; title=&quot;Lustre HSM support for a directory&#160;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13024&quot;&gt;LU-13024&lt;/a&gt;), since the directory and its subdirectories would not need to be released for this state to be useful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;However&lt;/em&gt;, it may be that this state (in &lt;tt&gt;trusted.hsm&lt;/tt&gt;?) could be used as the initial part of a directory stub, but the state could only be &lt;tt&gt;HS_EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; and/or &lt;tt&gt;HS_ARCHIVED&lt;/tt&gt; (if all of the files in that directory are known to be archived) and never &lt;tt&gt;HS_RELEASED&lt;/tt&gt; (because we don&apos;t yet support the HSM coordinator to automatically create the stubs in a directory when it is accessed, though this would definitely be useful).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
